long_desc.thetext:
description: Live preview does not work.
build version: v2.3.0 20080114-0800
steps to reproduce: 1. Make sure the Enable Live Preview in chart builder option is selected. 2. New a datasource with sample DB and new a dataset with table customers. 3. Insert a chart, bind the dataset. Select customername as Category series, select creditlimit as Value series. 4. Check the Chart Preview pane.
Expected result: Live Preview works, that is X Axis is rendered with customer names and Y Axis is rendered with creditlimit.
Actual result: Live Preview does not work, that is X Axis is renderred A,B,C and Y Axis is rendered with 2,4,6,8...

More info: I find I can only reproduce this bug with the first report I made today. I don't know why. Please see attached report. However, Live Preview does not work when chart is bound to a cube. Please have a check.

(In reply to comment #1) > More info: > I find I can only reproduce this bug with the first report I made today. I > don't know why. Please see attached report. However, Live Preview does not work > when chart is bound to a cube. Please have a check. > In your attached report, the SortKey of category series is set error, so the live preview does not work. And so far live preview doesn't support cube.
